  "verdict": {
    "framing": "IDENTIFIABILITY finding, not 'defeats the standard toolbox'. The dividing line is latent-awareness, not interventions: GIES gets the same interventional budget as the reference and recovers the skeleton well (SHD 2.37) but, assuming causal sufficiency, still reports the hidden-confounded pair as causal in most worlds (17/35); PC/FCI likewise (13/8). Only the latent-aware interventional rule keeps confounded-kept at 0.",
    "known_circularity": "These worlds are admitted by the reference grader itself (gate T3), so admission and the headline are not yet decoupled. Next milestone: grader-independent admission + an information-fair crossover + varsortability/variance-standardization control + a name-only LLM baseline that should score at chance.",
    "seed_fix": "Independent per-environment seeds for GIES (was aliasing the obs+do envs to one seed, which had inflated GIES skeleton-SHD to 6.66; now 2.37 \u2014 a fairer comparison).",
    "ges": "GES errors on every world (causal-learn GES is numpy-2 incompatible)."
  }
}